{
  "stem": "20142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was-- we supposed to return on September 1 to school when they came over the news-- there were two weeks prior to the outbreak of the war that there were movement of Polish armies from place to place, and armaments, and so on.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew that something was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we did believe in the strength of the Polish army to such extent that we didn't give a second thought that it will be so quickly devastated.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But this was slowly building up in us that World War II is unavoidable.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After what happened to Austria, Czechoslovakia, and we knew that Hitler would try to get Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it actually happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We got the news of the outbreak of the war, of the attack on Poland, early morning hours of the September 1, 1939.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And within a few weeks, Lodz was captured and we started to learn how to deal with Germans, who the Germans are, and how to-- what did they expect to do with us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that was on the fourth or fifth of September.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So very quickly, within a week, I think, they were in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And with them came the Einsatzgruppen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know them, who they were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they were [INAUDIBLE] they already started to set up certain points, demanding certain things from population.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like labor and getting rid of-- expecting all the gold, silver, and valuables to be surrendered to Germans under the protect-- under the warning that in case they will be found on the person there will be death penalty without any court.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were limitation of food and people has to stay in line.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
